---
title: Sticky Hoisin Chicken with roasted broccoli and noodles
description: Hoisin is a thick, sweet and salty sauce popular in Cantonese cuisine. It's most commonly used to marinate meat or poultry which is why in this recipe it pairs perfectly with succulent roast chicken thighs and tender veg.
